This paper focuses on optimizing the efficiency of DRAM caching through software-hardware cooperation, which falls under the category of computer systems and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of frequency-based replacement policies, which is related to performance analysis and optimization (cs.PF). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed design through extensive experiments, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of in-package DRAM, which is related to digital circuits (cs.DC) and system-level design and simulation (cs.SY).
